Commentary: big appeal, and umpire Palliyaguruge says not out. Excellent delivery, angling in and straightening towards off stump from a good length. Latham is stuck on the crease and hit on the back leg. Looks close on replay too - not sure why Bangladesh didn't review this. Height may be an issue. It is, according to Hawkeye, which says it's comfortably missing the top of off

Commentary: and again, angles in before nipping away off the seam. Shorter and in the corridor, and Latham pokes and misses

Commentary: gone, what a great sequence of deliveries this is. Again some seam away from the left-hander, but this time he pitches it full and outside off stump, enticing the drive away from the body. Latham obliges, and sends a thin edge to Liton Das behind the stumps. The length was just perfect, because it was full without being a half-volley, and there was just enough of distance between where the ball pitched and where it met Latham's edge for it to move that small, lethal amount
